## Query Patterns

### Basic Queries

```typescript
// Simple filter
const q = query(
  collection(db, 'transactions'),
  where('user_id', '==', userId),
  where('status', '==', 'completed')
);

// Ordering
const q = query(
  collection(db, 'transactions'),
  orderBy('date', 'desc'),
  limit(10)
);

// Range queries
const q = query(
  collection(db, 'transactions'),
  where('amount', '>=', 100),
  where('amount', '<=', 500)
);
```

### Composite Queries

```typescript
// Requires composite index
const q = query(
  collection(db, 'transactions'),
  where('user_id', '==', userId),
  where('status', '==', 'completed'),
  orderBy('date', 'desc')
);

// Firestore will prompt you to create index
// Follow the link in console error
```

### Array Queries

```typescript
// Check if array contains value
const q = query(
  collection(db, 'users'),
  where('household_ids', 'array-contains', householdId)
);

// Check if any value in array matches any in list
const q = query(
  collection(db, 'users'),
  where('roles', 'array-contains-any', ['admin', 'editor'])
);
```

